description: Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny's body has been returned to his mother, his spokesperson said Saturday.
title: Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny’s body returned to his mother, spokesperson says

description: South Korea and the United States flew advanced stealth fighters in a joint missile-interception drill Friday over the Korean Peninsula, South Korea’s air force said, an apparent response to a spate of weapons tests this year by rival North Korea.
title: US and South Korea fly warplanes in interception drills after North Korea’s missile test

description: TEL AVIV — Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has unveiled his first official postwar plan for Gaza — but experts say the proposal has more to do with political posturing than an offer of a tangible strategy for the months and years ahead.
title: Netanyahu’s postwar plan for Gaza reflects difficult balancing act, experts say

description: Officials in Spain are working to find shelter for displaced residents after a deadly fire killed at least 10 people and injured more than a dozen.
title: Spain apartment complex fire kills at least 10

description: Two years after the war began, Ukraine is struggling on the battlefield and to maintain support from the United States. NBC News' chief foreign correspondent Richard Engel reports on the state of the war from one of the front lines.
title: On second anniversary of war, Ukraine struggles to fight on
